text: Ágnes Gee (born 29 August 1974) is a Hungarian former professional tennis player. She was previously known as Ágnes Muzamel. Gee, who was born in Budapest, appeared in seven Federation Cup ties for Hungary in the early 1990s, while competing on the professional tour. From 1996 to 1999 she played college tennis for the University of Mississippi (Ole Miss). A four-time All- American, she was an NCAA singles quarter-finalist in 1998.
